ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.commands

Class GestureCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.AbstractAction
      • ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.commands.AbstractCommand
        • ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.commands.DelegatedCommand
          • ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.commands.GestureCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ActionListener, Serializable, Cloneable, EventListener, Action

    public final class GestureCommand
extends DelegatedCommand
    The command used by editors to recognize and process gestures. The source of the ActionEvent used to activate a gesture command must be a GestureEvent or an exception will be thrown when attempting to perform the action. Strange Eons normally takes care of this, but if you are simulating a gesture you will need to create an appropriate event. If you wish to process gestures on a non-Commandable target, refer to GestureToolkit.
    Since:
    3.0
    See Also:
